### Attack Path

In teku we try to retrieve columns during DA check, but since we haven't subscribed to subnets and proper peers in advance, there is no guarantee that we will be able to retrieve the needed columns, especially if we have more columns to custody and retrieve ( if cgc update is huge, for example from 8 to 40 columns to custody, but whatever it is, its still critical, because we will subscribe to those subnets in next epoch, not now, which could be 30 slots away )

Given 32 slots per epoch, by default, the flow is the following:
1. CGC update is triggered at slot 2 (or any other slot after 1 ) of Epoch N
2. Sampling size + CGC ENR is updated immediately
3. Subnets are processed once per Epoch, so since they were already updated at slot 1, we will get the next subnet update  at slot 0 of Epoch N+1, which is way ahead, 31 slots!
4. DA check in `DataColumnSidecarAvailabilityChecker.initiateDataAvailabilityCheck` in the forkchoice logic, will fail to complete on time, because we are not subscribed to the needed subnets & peers in advance. It could happen that we could get some via RPC, but there is no guarantee, especially if we have more columns to custody.

### Impact
The most vulnerable teku nodes would be the ones that custody a lot of columns, because they need a lot of subnets and a lot of different peers.

When CGC changes, we immediately also announce the change in the ENR, so this could lead to peer downscoring from other clients as we are false-advertising. ( so when they request via rpc, we won't be able to return them )

As mentioned, since CGC & sampling size change immediately, the bigger impact is that teku nodes will fail data availability checks and result in wrong fork-choice, thus consensus split + punishment from the network, as they would be stuck trying to retrieve the columns, while they are not subscribed to the peer subnets that distribute them. 

### PoC

For the PoC we will do java 2 tests, one showing that we dont update subnets when we update cgc, and one showing that when there are missing columns, we cannot complete DA check.

Test 1, place the whole following test class in `networking/eth2/src/test/java/tech/pegasys/teku/networking/eth2/DataColumnSidecarSubnetBackboneSubscriberTest.java`
```java
package tech.pegasys.teku.networking.eth2;


import org.apache.tuweni.units.bigints.UInt256;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import tech.pegasys.teku.infrastructure.unsigned.UInt64;
import tech.pegasys.teku.networking.eth2.gossip.subnets.DataColumnSidecarSubnetBackboneSubscriber;
