```

In this poc I build an Osaka payload, strip the blob tx from the txpool (so the EL has no local copy), submit the payload via `engine_newPayloadV4`, and then ask `engine_getBlobsV2` for the blobs. Because the handler only consults the txpool, `blobsResponse.Data` comes back `null`, and the test now asserts it should be non-null to expose the bug.

The run fails with `Expected blobsResponse.Data`not to be <null>`. confirming Nethermind cannot serve blobs for the freshly proposed block.

## Impact
The consensus layer cannot fetch mandatory blob sidecars for privately sourced payloads, causing the block to be flagged data-unavailable. A proposer repeating this can stall ≥33 % of validators

## Recommendation

Persist blob bodies/proofs for every processed block (even if the tx never sat in the pool) or serve `engine_getBlobsV2` from canonical blocks rather than the pool.

`BlobAndProofV2` exposes only blob and proofs. There is no field for the KZG commitment that corresponds to the requested `blob_versioned_hash`.

`GetBlobsHandlerV2` simply wraps `txPool.TryGetBlobAndProofV1` and returns that two-item tuple. The commitment is never fetched or marshalled back to the caller.

https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/914b082efca9ae93990ebc849fe8d5169511a4f5/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Merge.Plugin/Handlers/GetBlobsHandlerV2.cs#L39-L55

```csharp
ArrayPoolList<BlobAndProofV2> response = new(request.Length);

        try
        {
            foreach (byte[] requestedBlobVersionedHash in request)
            {
                if (txPool.TryGetBlobAndProofV1(requestedBlobVersionedHash, out byte[]? blob, out byte[][]? cellProofs))
                {
                    response.Add(new BlobAndProofV2(blob, cellProofs));
                }
                else
                {
                    // fail if we were not able to collect full blob data
                    response.Dispose();
                    return ReturnEmptyArray();
                }
            }
```

By contrast, `engine_getPayloadV5` returns `BlobsBundleV2`, which does expose the commitments together with the blobs and cell proofs that were used when the payload was built 

The consensus-side spec for 4844/PeerDAS expects the same triple (blob, commitment, proofs) in the sidecar so that the CL can verify the cell proofs against the exact commitment the EL used.

https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/914b082efca9ae93990ebc849fe8d5169511a4f5/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Merge.Plugin/Data/BlobsBundleV2.cs#L23

```csharp
foreach (Transaction? tx in block.Transactions)
            {
                blobsCount += tx?.GetBlobCount() ?? 0;
            }

            Commitments = new byte[blobsCount][];
            Blobs = new byte[blobsCount][];
            Proofs = new byte[blobsCount * Ckzg.CellsPerExtBlob][];
            int blockIndex = 0;

            foreach (Transaction? tx in block.Transactions)
            {
                if (!tx.SupportsBlobs)
                {
                    continue;
                }

                if (tx is not { NetworkWrapper: ShardBlobNetworkWrapper { Version: ProofVersion.V1 } wrapper })
                {
                    throw new ArgumentException("Shard blob transaction should contain network wrapper data");
```


Without the commitment in the V2 response an honest CL must recompute it locally and can no longer directly compare what the EL hands out via `engine_getBlobsV2` with the commitment it previously advertised (e.g. in builder overrides or fork-choice rewinds). That divergence is exactly what the spec update was intended to eliminate.

