### Summary


**Threat Classification**


Type: Memory Safety Violation

Affected: Consensus layer clients

Trigger: Malicious P2P request




**Technical Background**

EIP-7917: Deterministic Proposer Lookahead:

Precomputes proposer assignments for next N epochs

Stores in proposer_lookahead array in beacon state

Array size: PROPOSER_LOOKAHEAD_SLOTS ÷ SLOTS_PER_EPOCH = 256 ÷ 32 = 8 entries

Purpose: Enables MEV-boost, block building optimizations, validator preparation.




**The Vulnerable Code Pattern**


From Fusaka Auditor Guide:

"BeaconState::get_beacon_proposer_index: uses proposer lookahead to return proposer"



Pseudocode Implementation:


pub struct BeaconState {
    pub slot: Slot,  // Current slot (u64)
    pub proposer_lookahead: [ValidatorIndex; 8],  // 8 epochs ahead
    // ... other fields
}

impl BeaconState {
    pub fn get_beacon_proposer_index(
        &self,
        requested_slot: Slot
    ) -> Result<ValidatorIndex> {
        // Calculate epoch offset
        let offset = (requested_slot - self.slot) / SLOTS_PER_EPOCH;

        // VULNERABLE: No bounds checking!
        Ok(self.proposer_lookahead[offset])
    }
}




**Vulnerability #1: Integer Underflow**

Attack: Request Past Slot


current_slot = 10000
requested_slot = 9999  // One slot in the past

// Unsigned integer subtraction
offset = (9999 - 10000) / 32
       = (-1) / 32  // Wraps in unsigned arithmetic
       = (u64::MAX) / 32
       = 576460752303423487  // Massive index

// Array access
proposer = state.proposer_lookahead[576460752303423487]
// OUT OF BOUNDS - crashes validator


In Rust:

Debug mode: Panic with overflow error

Release mode: Wraps to u64::MAX, then accesses invalid memory




**Vulnerability #2: Array Bounds Overflow**


Attack: Request Beyond Lookahead


current_slot = 10000
requested_slot = 10300  // 9 epochs ahead (beyond 8 epoch lookahead)

offset = (10300 - 10000) / 32 = 300 / 32 = 9

// Array only has indices 0-7 (8 entries)
proposer = state.proposer_lookahead[9]  // OUT OF BOUNDS
Consequences:

Rust: Panic crash

Go: Panic crash

C++: Undefined behavior (could read garbage, corrupt memory, or crash)





